ἱ Marginal in OA. Omitted in OB, LA, ΟΕ, Υ, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΟ, MD. Seemingly an addinb belonging to (ΙΙ) alone, and therefore not from Bracton. ·

F. 196, ll. 5-10. Etcamveras....d0miat1n V this passage is duplicated in ll. 41-46, at which place it is found in OB, OD, OC, MA, ΜΒ, MD, ΜΕ, CM, Y. Inserted aster ipsura, l. 87, in OF; aster iusticiarium, l. 29, in LA, MC. Marginal in OA. Omitted in ΟΕ. From Bronton.

F. 1961),11. 35-36. Est enim sonus. . . . et sauros alterius. Regular in OB, OF, OC, OD, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΟ, ΜΕ, LA. Marginal in OA. Omitted in ΟΕ, Υ. This is accounted for by all three of the larger groups, and is therefore from Bracton.

F. 197, 119-27. De libertate licet. . . . mairam. Regular in OB, OD, MA. ΜΒ, ΜΟ, MD, ME, LA. Inserted afcerlrabueril, trutmonia OF, B (marks additional). Marginal in OA. Omitted in ΟΕ, Y. A passage vouched for by the particular manuscripts which support this has almost certainly come from Bracton.

F. 1971),11.7-8. Sed nemo. . . . respectibus. Regular in OF, OC, MC, MD, MI, LA. Marginal in OA. Omitted in OB, OD, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΕ, ΟΕ, Υ. In all probability from Bracton.

F. 198,ll.11-25. Nec praeiudicabitur. . . . corneum partiam. Regular in OD, ΜΕ, LA. Inserted asterrcbus sats, l. 12,1. 1971), in ΟΟ; asternatata, l. 26, f. 1971), in OF; alter adano, l. 26, in OB, MA, ΜΒ, ΜΟ, MD, ΟΕ, Υ. Marginal in OA. Clearly an addicio from Bracton himself.

F . 199, ll. 13-26. Vel iuratum. . . . uliud erit. Regular in OA, OB, OD, MA, MB, MC, MD, LA, ΟΕ, Υ. Inserted after oausam, l. 9, in OC, OF, CB. From Bracton.

F. 291, ll. 19-26. Cum aulem . . . . superflua Regular in OD. Inserted after remanere, l. 35, in ΟΟ, ΜΟ, MD, ΜΕ, LA, CA; aster panci- pio, l. 41, in OF, ΜΙ, B(marks additional). Marginal in OA. Omitted in OB, MA, ΜΒ, ΟΕ, Υ. Another case of (ΙΙ) and (ΙΙΙ) vouching for an addida from Bracton which (Ι) omits. ¹
